    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1c459a7f_49222e18",
        "filename": "util/ios/exception_processor.mm",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 44,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-02T20:52:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e How do I know the first Os version is 10.15.0?  For now I\u0027ll put 10.15 everywhere...\n\nLook in the different OS directories on opensource.apple.com. objc4 was 756.2 in https://opensource.apple.com/release/macos-10146.html and then 779.1 in https://opensource.apple.com/release/macos-1015.html. You can also look to https://opensource.apple.com/source/objc4/ or https://opensource.apple.com/tarballs/objc4/ to figure out what the most recent source-released version is.",
